Deadeye						KEY:Deadeye ~ Deeds				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.Deed	PRECLASS:1,Gunslinger=1		VISIBLE:YES											SOURCEPAGE:p.3		DESC:You can target touch AC beyond your firearm's first range increment. Performing this deed costs 1 grit point per range increment beyond the first. You still take the Ð2 penalty on attack rolls for each range increment beyond the first when you perform this deed.
Quick Clear					KEY:Quick Clear ~ Deeds			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Deed	PRECLASS:1,Gunslinger=1		VISIBLE:YES											SOURCEPAGE:p.3		DESC:As a standard action, you can remove the broken condition from a single firearm you are currently wielding, as long as that condition was gained by a firearm misfire. This deed costs 1 grit point to perform.
Pistol-whip					KEY:Pistol-whip ~ Deeds			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.Deed	PRECLASS:1,Gunslinger=3		VISIBLE:YES											SOURCEPAGE:p.3		DESC:You can make a surprise melee attack with the butt or handle of you firearm as a standard action. When you do, you are considered to be proficient with the firearm as a melee weapon (gaining a +2 bonus on the attack roll) and gain a bonus on the attack and damage rolls equal to the enhancement bonus of the firearm. The damage dealt by the pistol-whip is of the bludgeoning type, and is determined by the size of the firearm. One-handed firearms deal 1d6 points of damage (1d4 if wielded by size Small creatures) and two-handed firearms deal 1d10 points of damage (1d8 if wielded by size Small creatures). Regardless of your size, the critical multiplier of this attack is 20/x2. If the attack hits, you can make a CMB check to knock the target prone as a free action. Performing this deed costs 1 grit point.
Gunslinger Initiative		KEY:Gunslinger Initiative ~ Deeds	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Deed	PRECLASS:1,Gunslinger=3	VISIBLE:YES											SOURCEPAGE:p.4		DESC:As long as you have at least 1 grit point, you gain a +2 bonus on initiative checks. If you also have the Quick Draw feat, your hands are free and unrestrained, and the firearm is not hidden, you can draw a single firearm as part of the initiative check.
Covering Shot				KEY:Covering Shot ~ Deeds		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialQuality.Extraordinary.Deed	PRECLASS:1,Gunslinger=7		VISIBLE:YES											SOURCEPAGE:p.4		DESC:As an immediate reaction, when you miss with a firearm attack, you can spend 1 grit point to pin down the target of that missed attack. The pinned-down target is treated as if it were entangled for 1 round. You cannot choose to purposely miss a target to gain this effect.
Targeting					KEY:Targeting ~ Deeds			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.Deed	PRECLASS:1,Gunslinger=7		VISIBLE:YES											SOURCEPAGE:p.4		DESC:As a swift action, you can take aim for greater accuracy and effect. On the next firearm attack you make before the end of her turn, you can choose part of the body to target, and gain the following effects depending on the part of the body targeted. If a creature does not have one of the listed body locations, that body location cannot be targeted. This deed costs 1 grit point to perform no matter the part of the creature you target. Creatures that are immune to sneak attack are immune to these effects.
Bleeding Wound				KEY:Bleeding Wound ~ Deeds		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:SpecialAttack.Extraordinary.Deed	PRECLASS:1,Gunslinger=11	VISIBLE:YES											SOURCEPAGE:p.4		DESC:When you hit a living creature with a firearm attack, you can spend 1 grit point as a free action to have that attack deal extra %1 bleed damage. Alternatively, you can spend 2 grit points to deal 1 point of Strength, Dexterity, or Constitution bleed damage (your choice) instead. Creatures that are immune to sneak attacks are also immune to either type of bleed damage.|DEX
